added.title: Ghosts Schmosts
added.description: Seth leads a group of kids into a haunted mine in an effort to prove that everything has a scientific explanation and that there's no reason to be afraid ghosts. But things get spooky when they encounter a ghost that Seth doesn't have a scientific explanation for. Seth has to learn to give into his fear in order to and solve the mystery of the mine ghost.

added.title: Hide and Pam
added.description: Hide and Pam: Pam learns to play hide and seek a little too well./Chair Factory: Seth improves productivity at the Fancytown chair factory./Turtle: Seth brings a shy turtle for show and tell./Rainy Day: Cool James teaches the other kids how to have fun making music on a rainy day./Best Friends Club: Lil' Lemon and Nevin hold the first meeting of the Best Friends Club.

added.title: Peel of Fortune
added.description: Bugs and Daffy have a have a reversal of fortune, and Bugs is forced to return to his old rabbit hole.

added.title: Double Date
added.description: Lola gives Daffy dating advice, and falls in love with him in the process. But Daffy only has eyes for Tina, and Bugs is surprised to discover that he might actually have feelings for Lola.

added.title: To Bowl or Not to Bowl
added.description: In a bid to defeat his nemesis at the big bowling tournament, Daffy has to swallow his pride and ask for Bugs' help.

added.title: Newspaper Thief
added.description: Daffy sets out to find who has been stealing Bugs' newspaper.

added.title: Bugs & Daffy Get a Job
added.description: Bugs decides to enter the workforce, as Daffy decides to get plastic surgery.

added.title: Never Trust a Human
added.description: A flashback episode tells the story of Young Wu and Young Garmadon meeting Aspheera and teaching her the secrets of Spinjitzu.

added.title: Under Siege
added.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

added.title: The Explorer's Club
added.description: The ninja must break into the Explorer's Club to obtain the second Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu, running afoul of the club's manager and irate club-members.

added.title: Vengeance Is Mine!
added.description: Aspheera arrives at the Monastery of Spinjitzu and confronts Wu, forcing one of the ninja to make a heroic sacrifice.

added.title: A Cold Goodbye
added.description: Having learned Zane is not dead, Master Wu prepares to go after him, but Lloyd and the other ninja take matters into their own hands and defy their Master.

added.title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 1
added.description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

added.title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 2
added.description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

added.title: #Frenemies Part 1
added.description: Batgirl's worlds collide when her best friend from Gotham City moves to Metropolis. Meanwhile, Catwoman is making some new friends of her own.

added.title: Prince Starling's Quest
added.description: Lion-O is happily playing with Snarf in their "Frolicking Field" and doesn't have a care in the world, unfortunately he's accidentally stomping all over the miniature village of the Micrits! The tiny people want to defeat the "giant orange monster" but such a quest would require a brave hero. Luckily, the Micrits have such a hero: Prince Starling! Now, let us the tell you the epic tale of Prince Starling as he journeys to find the fountain of growth and defeat the wicked Lion-O, who has no idea any of this is going on!

added.title: Lion-S
added.description: Lion-O and the other ThunderCats are thrilled to meet a brand new Thunderian: Lion-S! She's cool, good at fighting robots and, most importantly, thinks Lion-O and his Sword of Omens are really neat and interesting! Looks like the ThunderCats have a new best friend! Maybe even, a new ThunderCat?????

added.title: Snarf's Day Off
added.description: Hey everyone, it's Snarf's monthly day off! That's right, this episode follows Snarf as he leaves Cats' Lair to get a needed vacation, by transforming into a normal cat and hanging out with a nice old lady on a farm! But his relaxing day is threatened when Snarf and the nice old lady cross paths with Mumm-Ra!

added.title: Mumm-Ra of Plun-Darr Part 1
added.description: The Thundercats' worst nightmare comes true when their worst enemies, Mumm-Ra and The Mutants, team up after Mumm-Ra acquires The Sword of Plun-Darr!

added.title: Mumm-Ra of Plun-Darr Part 2
added.description: Chaos reigns over Third Earth now that the Mutants and Mumm-Ra control the Cats' Lair! The Thundercats' only hope is to sneak back in and get a super secret weapon Panthro has hidden at the heart of the Lair.

added.title: King Axel
added.description: After a screening of the King Arthur tale, Axel holds out his sword and declares himself king, but when Dynamo uses his magnetism to steal the weapon and bestow it upon Masko, it casts doubt among the team over who is the true leader.

added.title: The Trojan Bear
added.description: When Axel opens a subscription gift-box he didn't even order, the team finds their ranks divided by a robotic bear - or Princess SugarSalt in disguise!

added.title: Party On
added.description: As Zoe preps Cleo LeBall's birthday party, Axel and the team run damage control against a jealous crasher - Princess SugarSalt, who has turned the decorations and gifts into instruments of chaos!

added.title: Bringing Up Baby
added.description: Zoe leaves Axel in charge of the school project - watching over an infant simulator doll - but when MadCap brings the doll to life, Axel and the team must stop the baby without damaging it or risk getting a failing grade!

added.title: Magnus P.I.
added.description: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself./Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan.  Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

added.title: Awesome Brawlers Training  Camp
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned./Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Begins/Riot vs. Ajit
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Begins: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve./Riot vs. Ajit: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

added.title: Kung Fu Master/A Battle of Popularity
added.description: Kung Fu Master: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!/A Battle of Popularity: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

added.title: The Mysterious Revenger/Wynton vs. Lia
added.description: The Mysterious Revenger: It's the quarter finals of the Bakugan Battle League, the top eight brawlers are set to face off! In this round, Dan will face off against the Bakugan rocker - Revenger! These two brawlers give it their all in this icy cold clash!/Wynton Vs. Lia: The quarter finals continue, and it's the first Awesome Brawler vs. Awesome Brawler matches of the Bakugan Battle League tournament. In this round, it's Wynton vs. Lia and Shun vs. Lightning.

added.title: Jamas Confies en un Humano
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Sitiados
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que el Maestro Wu es el "Traicionero", los ninja se encuentran asediados en el Monasterio, tratando de proteger a Wu de la ira de Aspheera.

added.title: El Club de Exploradores
added.description: El ninja debe entrar en el Club del Explorador para obtener el segundo Pergamino de Spinjitzu Prohibido, en conflicto con el gerente del club y los miembros furiosos del club.

added.title: La Venganza es Mia
added.description: Aspheera llega al Monasterio de Spinjitzu y se enfrenta a Wu, obligando a uno de los ninjas a hacer un sacrificio heroico.

added.title: Una Fria Despedida
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que Zane no está muerto, el Maestro Wu se prepara para ir tras él, pero Lloyd y el otro ninja toman el asunto en sus propias manos y desafían a su Maestro.

added.title: El Oso Troyano
added.description: Cuando Axel abre una caja de regalo de suscripción que ni siquiera ordenó, el equipo encuentra sus filas divididas por un oso robótico, io la Princesa SugarSalt disfrazada!

added.title: Sed de Poder
added.description: Axel y sus juguetes despliegan el Joyride en una batalla de "barco" a "barco" contra el Dr. Nautilus, quien ha perforado una tubería de agua para inundar las alcantarillas y se ha establecido como "Almirante Nautilus".

added.title: Que Comience la Fiesta
added.description: Mientras Zoe prepara la fiesta de cumpleaños de Cleo LeBall, Axel y el equipo controlan los daños contra una estrelladora celosa: ila princesa SugarSalt, que ha convertido las decoraciones y los regalos en instrumentos de caos!

added.title: Criando Bebe
added.description: Zoe deja a Axel a cargo del proyecto escolar, vigilando una muñeca simulador de bebés, pero cuando MadCap da vida a la muñeca, iAxel y el equipo deben detener al bebé sin dañarlo o correr el riesgo de obtener una calificación reprobatoria!

added.title: Rey Axel
added.description: Después de una proyección de la historia del Rey Arturo, Axel extiende su espada y se declara rey, pero cuando Dynamo usa su magnetismo para robar el arma y dársela a Masko, arroja dudas entre el equipo sobre quién es el verdadero líder.
